<HEAD>London Jewelry Dealer Bought Largest Diamond Ever Sold At Auction</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> jewelry dealer was identified as the person who paid $ 9.13 million for the largest diamond ever to be sold at auction, a Sotheby's spokeswoman said. <PERSON> Laurence </PERSON> <PERSON> Graff </PERSON> purchased the 85.91-carat, pear-shaped diamond by telephone during Tuesday's auction, spokeswoman <PERSON> Jennifer </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> said Wednesday. The sale set a record for any gem sold at auction, she said. The diamond, which was perfectly cut and flawless, was part of an auction that brought $ 36 million, a record for a jewelry sale in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. The auction included gems belonging to the late <PERSON> Clare </PERSON> <PERSON> Boothe </PERSON> <PERSON> Luce </PERSON>, a former congresswoman and ambassador to <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION>. Also Wednesday, <PERSON> Christie </PERSON>'s announced the sale of a 52.59 carat diamond ring for $ 7.8 million, the highest price ever paid per carat at auction, said spokeswoman <PERSON> Lily </PERSON> <PERSON> Zimmerman </PERSON>. She said $ 132,000 was paid per carat by a private Saudi Arabian collector bidding by telephone.
