<HEAD>Rabbi Says Convent at Auschwitz Being Renovated</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Roman Catholic Carmelite convent on the grounds of <LOCATION> Auschwitz </LOCATION> is being renovated, French Rabbi <PERSON> Daniel </PERSON> <PERSON> Fahri </PERSON> said after visiting the World War II Nazi death camp in <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION>. Jews by the hundreds of thousands died in <LOCATION> Auschwitz </LOCATION>'s gas chambers. The international Jewish community opposed plans to establish a convent there and an agreement was signed Feb. 22 in <LOCATION> Geneva </LOCATION> to move the convent to a nearby location within two years. <PERSON> Fahri </PERSON> said on Wednesday, `` During a pilgrimage I organized at <LOCATION> Auschwitz </LOCATION> on April 17, I could see that the building housing the convent had been completely sandblasted, both inside and outside. `` The facade and the roofing of the convent have been completely redone. Last year, the building was simply falling apart.'' He said a deputy archbishop at <LOCATION> Krakow </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION>, seemed `` embarrassed'' when asked about the renovations and `` ended up by saying he did n't know anything.''
