<HEAD>Dollar Higher, Stocks Lower In Tokyo Morning Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The dollar finished higher Thursday against the Japanese yen in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>, while stock prices lost slightly. The dollar ended the day at 124.30 yen, up 0.40 yen from its close of 123.90 yen Wednesday. It had opened the day at 124.27 yen and fluctuated in narrow range of 124.20 yen to 124.36 yen. `` The dollar is somewhat strengthened following overnight dollar-purchasings in overseas markets and the selling of European currencies,'' said an exchange dealer at a major commercial bank in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>. The dealer, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said a <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Labor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> report Wednesday that <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> consumer prices jumped 0.5 percent during March had no major impact on the currency market. `` The worsening figures were what many expected,'' the dealer said. On the <ORGANIZATION> Tokyo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average, a 207.09-point winner Wednesday, shed a light 35.93 points, or 0.13 percent, closing the day at 26,828.16. `` The third consecutive setback on Wall Street overnight prompted a sense of uncertainty over market propects among investors,'' said an official of a major securities firm, speaking on condition of anonymity. He said trading was thin as institutional investors stayed out of the market.
