 organized campaign to rig a local election might work. Ms. <PERSON> Nevins </PERSON> admitted she broke the law, but said it was the only way to test the potential for fraud. Mrs. <PERSON> Dolen </PERSON> claimed that fraudulent registration was rare, but breaking the law on television would encourage others to do it. `` I told her, ` If you go on television, people who have never thought about doing something like this will think about doing so.' I think she's really out of line,'' she said.
