<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> observed a cease-fire today in their seven-week `` war of the cities'' after <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> fired missiles into the holy city of <LOCATION> Qom </LOCATION> and said it would stop firing if <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> also did. <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s navy commander said his warships fought a `` heroic battle'' against <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> forces in the <LOCATION> Persian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> on Monday and charged the Americans fired on his men in the water after they abandoned their vessels. The unofficial cease-fire, which <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> said would begin at midnight -LRB- 4 p.m. EDT Wednesday -RRB-, appeared to be holding despite an all-out mobilization declared by <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> to confront the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION>. During their 7 -LCB- - year war, <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> have observed several temporary cease-fires when one side offered to stop firing if it had the last shot The bombardments usually resume after a short period. The official <ORGANIZATION> Iraqi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION>, monitored in <LOCATION> Nicosia </LOCATION>, said <LOCATION> Iraqi </LOCATION> troops fired two long-range missiles into <LOCATION> Qom </LOCATION> at 11:45 p.m. and said they would be the last if <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> did not retaliate. <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s official <ORGANIZATION> Islamic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION>, also monitored in <LOCATION> Cyprus </LOCATION>, said several civilians were killed and others wounded when the missiles exploded in residential areas of the holy city, 100 miles south of <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION> and the seat of <LOCATION> Iran </LOC