n no investigation of those paramilitary groups?'' Amnesty said that in July and August political repression in <LOCATION> Colombia </LOCATION> entered `` a new phase, and the country is in the grip of a human rights emergency.'' In those two months anonymously authored ` hit lists' of prominent Colombians were published and a wave of killings of students, university lecturers and human rights leaders in <LOCATION> Medellin </LOCATION> was reported. Amnesty said `` hundreds of case studies show that killings and ` disappearances' blamed on the ` death squads' were in fact carried out by police and military personnel.''
