<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Entertainer <PERSON> Eartha </PERSON> <PERSON> Kitt </PERSON> sings and speaks in several languages _ a talent and a problem, she says. `` When I was growing up in <LOCATION> Harlem </LOCATION>,'' she said, `` a number of people from the <LOCATION> Caribbean </LOCATION> were moving into the neighborhood. I wanted to play with the children, and they all spoke Spanish. Eventually, by talking about the games we were playing and that kind of thing, I began to learn their language.'' During shows this week, she sang in English, French and Japanese. She talked in English, Spanish and French. Some people accuse her of putting on airs. `` The black people think, ` She thinks she's white,''' she said. `` My mother was black and Cherokee Indian. My father was white, although nobody knows for sure who he was. Then my mother married a black man who did n't want any ` yellow gal' around the house. ... She gave me away.'' The outspoken singer was criticized for her trips to <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> despite that country's apartheid policies. `` I first went in 1974, because I was curious,'' she said. `` I wanted to see for myself. And they're still holding that against me.''
