<HEAD>Reagan Offers `Very Cynical' Joke Pegged To Middle East</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Reagan Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPRINGFIELD, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> told what he conceded was a `` very cynical'' joke Thursday as part of his response to a question about the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> at a world affairs forum here. After pledging efforts to secure talks between <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> and its Arab neighbors, <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> said: `` I ca n't resist telling you a little joke. It's kind of cynical _ very cynical in a matter of fact _ about the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>.'' In the joke, a scorpion comes to a creek and asks a frog to carry him across it, because scorpions ca n't swim. The frog says, `` Why, you'd sting me if I did.'' The scorpion responds, `` That'd be silly because if I stung you and you died, I'd drown.'' `` Well, that made sense to the frog so he said, ` get on,' and started ferry him across and in <LOCATION> midstream </LOCATION> the scoprion stung him,'' the president said. As both were dying, the frog asked the scorpion, `` Why did you do that _ now we're both going to die.'' `` And the scorpion said, ` This is the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>,''' the president concluded. The joke was greeted with laughter and applause by members of the <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Affairs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> of Western <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION>. In answering a question about the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> said that `` we are going to keep on trying as hard as we can'' to bring about talks between the <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> states and <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>.'' When asked whether the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> was willing to talk with the <LOCATION> Palestinians </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> said, `` Yes.'' He added that the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> `` refused on 