<SECOND>PM-Oil Prices,0245</SECOND>
<HEAD>Oil Futures Continue Sliding</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Profit-taking and quiet days in the <LOCATION> Persian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> following Monday's combat have helped sustain a slide in oil futures prices. At the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, contracts for May delivery of West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> crude, settled at $ 17.74 per barrel on Wednesday, down 29 cents from Tuesday, when they fell 49 cents. Among refined products, May contracts for wholesale unleaded gasoline ended at 51.42 cents per gallon, down 0.72 cent, while wholesale heating oil contracts closed at 49.31 cents per gallon, off 0.37 cent. <PERSON> Madison </PERSON> <PERSON> Galbraith </PERSON>, senior energy specialist at <ORGANIZATION> Merrill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lynch </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Futures </ORGANIZATION>, said the selling that began late Monday continued as no reports of renewed hostilities emerged from the <LOCATION> Persian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION>. Prices surged early Monday amid reports that <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> vessels had destroyed two offshore Iranian oil platforms, sunk an Iranian patrol boat and bombed two Iranian navy frigates while <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> had fired on at least two <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> vessels. Traders often fear that fighting in the area might hamper oil shipments, which could tend to drive prices higher. But because producers outside the area widely are expected to cover any shortfall, the combat-induced rally was short-lived. Prices began dropping late Monday and continued falling on Tuesday and Wednesday as traders cashed in gains made during Monday's climb. Some of the selling also was due to technical factors, <PERSON> Galbreath </PERSON> said.
