<SECOND>PM-Wall Street Closing,0127</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A sudden afternoon downdraft wiped out an early gain in the stock market today, leaving prices little changed from Wednesday. Analysts said swings in prices of stock-index futures prompted professionals engaged in program trading to sell the futures and buy individual stocks in the early going. At midafternoon, they said, the balance abruptly reversed and selling programs hit the stock market. Brokers said the effect was especially pronounced because many other investors have been shying away from the stock market lately, and thus contributing to its potential volatility. They noted that many stocks have n't responded much so far to generally strong earnings reports for the first quarter.
