nouncement at a price of about $ 54 a share, well below the $ 77 market price when the merger was announced Aug. 5, the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> alleged. The final merger price was $ 82 a share. The agency said it investigated after the surveillance department of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Dealers </ORGANIZATION>, which monitors over-the-counter trading, noticed unusually heavy trading activity in <ORGANIZATION> First </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jersey </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> prior to the merger announcement. National Westminster is the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> subsidiary of <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Westminister </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION>. Its acquisition of <ORGANIZATION> First </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jersey </ORGANIZATION> created a $ 15.8 billion bank holding company with 250 branches in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> and the metropolitan area.
