<HEAD>USG To Let Shareholders Vote On Lowering Takeover Defense</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Wednesday it would allow its stockholders to decide whether the company should drop its `` poison-pill'' takeover defense, which is a major impediment to a <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> group's $ 1.63 billion takeover attempt. But <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION> said the offer was conditioned on the willingness of the investor group, <ORGANIZATION> Desert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> L.P. </ORGANIZATION>, to extend the deadline for its takeover bid, a provision criticized by <ORGANIZATION> Desert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>. Desert Partners's offer of $ 42 a share cash for 85 percent of <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION>'s stock has been spurned as inadequate by the company, a maker of building materials. USG's poison pill seeks to make a hostile takeover prohibitively expensive by allowing management to issue more shares if a bidder acquires more than 20 percent of the company's stock. <ORGANIZATION> Desert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>, which owns about 9.8 percent of <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION>'s outstanding stock, repeatedly has called on USG to rescind the poison pill, and issued a statement that it was pleased <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION> was putting the issue to a shareholder vote However, the group criticized <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION>'s request for it to extend its offer through June 16 from its current expiration on Friday. Desert Partners said USG provided no assurance that it would refrain from taking other defensive moves during that time. `` The partnership reiterated that it is willing to negotiate all aspects of its offer, including price,'' the statement concluded. Efforts to reach Desert Partners for further comment beyond the statement were unsuccessful and a message was not immediately returned after business hours late Wednesday. USG announced late Wed